        "email": "autotest@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "autotest",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2014-09-08 19:54:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nOnyx Autotest started enforced review-dne-part-1 session.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "2481db142d30c5277b866be429f9ea89abcd4edb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 251,
        "name": "Bob Glossman",
        "email": "bob.glossman@intel.com",
        "username": "bogl",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-09-08 20:02:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nno need to make this dependent on anything. one advantage of breaking up into small patches like this is they can all be independent and land in any order.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "bec47ad2edc7581c9c4252c6b14478ae176b9b22",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 403,
        "name": "Autotest",
        "email": "autotest@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "autotest",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2014-09-08 20:02:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nOnyx Autotest started enforced review-dne-part-2 session.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "bdb96b9426d2e1cd9b0c65e67a05fa20a710af77",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 419,
        "name": "Frank Zago",
        "email": "fzago@cray.com",
        "username": "fzago.cray"
      },
      "date": "2014-09-08 20:12:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nCreating a branch for each patch is a pita, and doesn't buy anything.\nPlus these patches can be accepted in order, in one go. There's no need to cherry pick one here and there.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "25cff02576b603d063521505a1c07ae0b8e6cadd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 251,
        "name": "Bob Glossman",
        "email": "bob.glossman@intel.com",
        "username": "bogl",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-09-08 20:19:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI disagree. there is a big advantage in keeping them all independent, even if it is a pita as you say.  given the vagaries of our test framework lots of test runs randomly fail.  with a long dependent series they can't land until and unless all of them pass.  when they are independent and can land in any order each little mod can land as soon as it alone passes test.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "7dad021a4cebfd979c456d74946abd041f9130e4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 419,
        "name": "Frank Zago",
        "email": "fzago@cray.com",
        "username": "fzago.cray"
      },
      "date": "2014-09-08 21:54:42.000000000",
      "message": "Abandoned\n\nwill put in separate branch",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
